<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-03-20T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-03-20T18:00:00-05:00" n="140" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d140">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">847.24/775: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Minister in Australia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-03-20T19:00:00-04:00">March
                                        20, 1944—7 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>23. You are authorized with reference to the last paragraph of your
                                airmail dispatch No. 684 of February 1, 1944, to express our regret
                                at the Commonwealth Government’s position on the matter, and to
                                request its assistance in facilitating the completion of procurement
                                contracts. This view may be presented orally or by note, in your
                                discretion.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>